from david rind subject re erythromycin in article fiberman writes is erythromycin effective in treating pneumonia it depends on the cause of the pneumonia. for treating bacterial
pneumonia in young otherwise-healthy non-smokers, erythromycin
is usually considered the antibiotic of choice, since it covers
the two most-common pathogens: strep pneumoniae and mycoplasma
pneumoniae.
-- david rind